descript.abstract:
Polygons of City Limits, land, and water bodies. Does not extend far enough east to include Mercer Island or Bellevue landforms.
This feature class reflects the visual interface between land and water based upon our 1993 ortho photos. It essentially follows the 8 foot contour line, except where the ortho offered further clarification. That 8 foot contour line matches closest to what NAVD88 shows as "mean high water" (see official definition below) at 7.97 feet. MEAN HIGH WATER (MHW): "A tidal datum. The average of all the high water heights observed over the National Tidal Datum Epoch. For stations with shorter series, simultaneous observational comparisons are made with a control tide station in order to derive the equivalent datum of the National Tidal Datum Epoch." Source: http://co-ops.nos.noaa.gov/mapfinder/mhw.html
